8 ounce Broccoli
1 unit Microwavable Rice
2 ounce Garlic-Ginger Scallion Paste
½ ounce Peanuts
10 ounce Ground Pork
Salt
Pepper
Cooking Oil

• Wash and dry produce.
• Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add
pork* and season with salt and pepper. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until pork
begins to brown, 3 minutes (it’ll finish cooking
in the next step).

• Meanwhile, break up broccoli into bite-size
pieces if necessary. Massage rice in package to
break up grains.
• Add another drizzle of oil to pan with pork.
Add broccoli and rice; season with a big pinch
of salt and pepper. Stir to combine.
• Stir in 1⁄4 cup water (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Cover
pan with lid. Cook, undisturbed, until broccoli is
tender and pork is cooked through, 3-4 minutes.

• Remove pan from heat. Stir in garlic-ginger
scallion paste. Taste and season with salt and
pepper if desired.
• Lightly crush peanuts in their bag.
• Divide pork and rice skillet between bowls;
top with peanuts and serve.

***Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.***